During the {{ill|Genpei War|ja|源平合戦|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Genpei War|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 治承・寿永の乱|1=Genpei War|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q737542}}, the clan initially supported the [[:en:Taira clan|Taira Clan]] and participated in the [[:en:Battle of Ichi-no-Tani|Battle of Ichi-no-Tani]]. However, they later sided with the [[:en:Minamoto clan|Minamoto Clan]]. Their contributions at the [[:en:Battle of Dan-no-ura|Battle of Dan-no-ura]] earned them recognition, granting them dominion over the Asa District. The clan also participated in the [[:en:Mongol invasions of Japan|Mongol invasions of Japan]] (1274 and 1281) alongside the [[:en:Ōuchi clan|Ōuchi Clan]] under the orders of the [[:en:Kamakura shogunate|Kamakura Shogunate]].

